## Section 3: Threat Actors ##\

- Threat Actors:
    - Individuals or entities that are responsible for incidents impacting security of an organization. Categorized into the following 5 types:
        - Unskilled Attackers
        - Hacktivists
        - Organized Crime
        - Nation State Actors
        - Insider Threats
    - Motivations of Threat Actors are categorized under the following groups: (It is important to note that the *intent* and *motivation* of a threat actor are different)
        - Data Exfil
        - Blackmail
        - Philosophical / Political Beliefs - Primary motivation for hacktivists, actions will include things like data leaks or website defacement.
        - Ethical Reasons - This was reserved for instances of ethical hacking (penetration testing)
        - Espionage
        - Revenge - self explanatory
        - Service Disruption
        - Disruption or Chaos - Some people just want to watch the world burn.
        - Financial Gain 
        - War - In times where crippling infrastructure can be done without bombs, cyber warfare is a common activity of nation-state actors.

